<TITLE> AL, BNP pay tributes to war martyrs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 16 (bdnews24.com)--The ruling Awami League and main opposition BNP are observing the Victory Day on Wednesday by paying homage to the martyrs of independence war on the Victory Day. The ruling party leaders, led by presidium member Syeda Sajeda Chowdhury, paid tributes at the National Memorial at Savar at dawn. BNP, led by chairperson Khaleda Zia, also paid its respects later. AL leaders and supporters along with presidium member Obaidul Qader paid floral tributes to the portrait of 'Bangabandhu' Sheikh Mujibur Rahman at Dhanmondi. Qader told reporters, "Let's promise to build a 'digital Bangladesh' under the leadership of prime minister Sheikh Hasina. We want to build a happy and prosperous Bangladesh." Wounded freedom fighters then paid their respects by laying floral wreaths at the portrait and remained silent for one minute as a mark of respect to the nation's independence architect. They demanded war crimes trial without further delay. Other associate organisations of the AL also paid homage to the martyrs. The party took out a rally at 3pm from the Suhrawardy Udyan. Khaleda along with the party leaders and supporters visited the National Memorial at Savar in the wee hours. She laid floral wreaths at the grave of former president Ziaur Rahman at around 9am at at Sher-e-Bangla Nagar where thousands of people gathered. The former prime minister along with the newly appointed standing committee members prayed for Zia. Secretary-general Khandaker Delwar Hossain said, "Bangladesh was established by the sacrifice of millions of people in the Independence War. But we have not been able to spread the spirit of independence among the people until now." "Let's build a happy, prosperous and democratic Bangladeshthis will be our promise today," he told reporters. He also slammed the government for its controversial activities including the decision to change the name of Zia International Airport. BNP has taken a three-day programme to observe the Victory Day. The national and party flags have been hoisted at the party's Naya Paltan headquarters. A rally will be taken out at around 3pm o Thursday from the party office. bdnews
